<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-624-985  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 624 985.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Canadian Datasystems  Oct 1990 v22 n10 p92(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Fixing Canada's high-tech image. (Viewpoint)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Argyle, Ray.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Canada's high-technology industry is part of the global technologymarket and requires new strategies to participate in it.andP;  Theinformation technology industry in Canada should not be seen as ahome industry, but rather as a part of the world market.andP;  Canadahas produced many accounting software, data base management, andcomputer graphics products in addition to making strides intelecommunications, parallel processing and biotechnologyresearch.andP;  Marketers should treat these developments as Canada'scontribution to the world technology market rather than as purelyCanadian products.andP;  New strategies to promote developement includecreating programs to increase automation in Canadian businesses,reinforce the educational system, and increase government supportof exporters of software.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     CanadaWorld MarketHigh TechnologyCritique.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>